Spiced Chai Gingerbread Cookies
  --GIR

Chai spice:
2 tsp ground cinnamon
1 tsp ground ginger
1/4 tsp nutmeg
1/2 tsp all-spice
1 tsp ground cardamom

In a bowl, mix all the spices together until well combined.

Dough:
1 1/2 stick butter
2 tsp vanilla
1/3 c molasses
1/4 c dark brown sugar
1 egg
2 1/2 c ap flour
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp salt

Cream butter and sugar. When well incorporated, add egg, molasses and vanilla; mix well. Add flour, baking soda, and salt to chai blend, whisk until fully incorporated. Combine wet and dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly until it comes together in a ball (add more flour if too wet). Chill in refrigerator for at least 30 min. Take dough and roll out to ~1/3" thick. Dust dough lightly with flour (careful to not add too much) and cut using cuttes or mold of your choice (or scoop out 2 tbsp balls). Transfer to a parchment lined baking sheet and freeze for 30 min. Preheat oven to 375F. Bake for 10-12 min.

Glaze:
1 c powdered sugar
2 tbsp warm water

Combine in a small bowl. Drizzle over warm cookies and let cool to harden.
